As I was walking through the halls today I was so proud to be a part of this team. The teachers are working so hard to make the first day a special memory for your lovelies. The attention to detail is is a demonstration of their dedication.
The maintenance team have done an EXCEPTIONAL JOB making sure all is ready. Fresh lines were painted to help with dismissal. They also gave up one of their days off to make sure it was complete. Take a drive thru tomorrow if you're by the school. These lines are very important as they guide the children safely to their vehicles.
Being intentional in all we do!
~Mrs. Leimeister

post_text:
I don't know about you, but I am on information OVERLOAD! I'm trying to space out all the info so you have time to digest each piece. Attached are the dismissal guidelines. Here's the cliff note version.
1. Watch the staff members; follow their directions, be patient, and we will make it through the first day. After that, it's a cake walk!
2. Three lanes....
All grades may go in Lane 1 & 2.
Pre-K and K are restricted to Lane #1
Don't get in Lane 3 unless you're leaving.
3. Use your turn signals: it's the one on the left.
4. Wait for the adult to direct you.
5. This one is important...Don't run over the staff LOL
We don't have subs.
6. Arrival @ 7:45
7. Dismissal @ 3:00
8. Walkers Come and Go through the front.
That's it! If you're bored, read the attachment. Thanks for all you do! Only 4 days! WHOOT WHOOT!!!!

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1rsS9BNY7LMbbVWdKzFRbJIODRAsNSx-J/view?usp=sharing

DRIVE.GOOGLE.COM

post_text: My eyes fill with tears as I share this. I try not to be too sappy about all that‚Äôs going on but when I saw this, it so touched my heart I just couldn‚Äôt help but cry! This is one of the sweetest things I‚Äôve ever seen. In a time when teachers and students are mourning each other, a parent and teacher found a way to bring comfort to a little girl. The teacher sent home little paper dolls (similar to Flat Stanley). You see, the dolls are a rendition of the teacher and her assistant. The little girl sleeps with them, eats with them, plays with them. What a phenomenal idea. Focusing on what‚Äôs important.... a child‚Äôs heart!

So, I absolutely love research and I‚Äôve been reading and listening to several speakers about our immune system. Not a doctor, I don‚Äôt claim to be one but something we ALL know is that healthy eating and exercise is essential to a healthy immune system. Did you know that the workout Coach Creguer is providing every day at 9:15 is EXACTLY what the doctors ordered? The level of intensity he is taking us too gets our hearts pumping just enough to build our immune system, yet not too strenuous to defeat it. So, get those workout clothes on; login each morning at 9:15! And if you can‚Äôt make it at 9:15; they‚Äôre online and you can watch it later. As your children are home longer they will be spending more time online. Make this time online count. Join me at 9:15 for a GREAT WORKOUT!
~Mrs. Leimeister üòÖüòÖüòÖ
